  "texts": [
    "By means of world clouds, we can see that there is reasonable agreement in terms of the most common words in the reports and the questions asked to that report.",
    "For example, in both cases, the word \"risk\", \"emission\" or \"warming\" are present with similar frequency.",
    "Notwithstanding, we notice how the words \"impacts\" or \"adaptation\" are hardly visible in the questions world cloud despite being very prevalent in the IPCC reports.",
    "A fairly simple analysis of the questions across all tools can help steering, for example outreach materials after publication, targeting the broader community and customizing content for different user categories.",
    "A community of users can be created which interact with authors through specific chatbots to elicit aspects of the report in full spirit of knowledge co-creation (Mauser et al. 2013)."
  ],
